    "viz_sec7": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 7. Data-Driven Icons\n\nAttach a search that returns one row. The viz reads four specific column names:\n\n| SPL Column | Effect |\n|---|---|\n| `icon` | Overrides the icon name (sanitized to `lowercase_underscores`). Wins over `iconName` / `customIcon` / threshold-effect icon swap. |\n| `color` | Overrides icon color (hex). **Beats the threshold engine.** |\n| `label` | Sets label text and auto-enables label display. |\n| `<thresholdField>` (default `value`) | Drives the threshold engine. Band picked from formatter settings. |\n\n### Example — value drives band, label shows hostname, icon swaps via threshold\n\n```spl\n| stats avg(uptime) AS value, latest(host) AS label BY service\n| head 1\n```\n\nFormatter set to `thresholdIconLow=error`, `thresholdIconMid=warning`, `thresholdIconHigh=check_circle` → the icon swaps per-row based on which band `value` falls into.\n\n### Example — explicit icon + color from SPL\n\n```spl\n| makeresults\n| eval icon=if(failed_logins>10, \"warning\", \"check_circle\"),\n       color=if(failed_logins>10, \"#EF4444\", \"#22C55E\"),\n       label=\"Auth subsystem\"\n```\n\nThe explicit `color` column wins over the threshold engine, so the formatter threshold settings are ignored for icon color. Useful when you want full SPL control of every visual property.\n\n### Renaming the threshold field\n\nIf your SPL column isn't called `value`, point the engine at the right name:\n\n```json\n\"options\": {\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdField\": \"cpu_pct\"\n}\n```",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },

    "viz_sec8": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 8. Full Dashboard Studio JSON Example\n\nA single panel using every major feature — data-driven via `ds.search`, threshold engine, threshold effects, glow, label, and `setToken` drilldown.\n\n```json\n\"dataSources\": {\n  \"ds_health\": {\n    \"type\": \"ds.search\",\n    \"options\": { \"query\": \"| makeresults | eval value=42.1, label=\\\"Queue\\\"\" }\n  }\n},\n\"visualizations\": {\n  \"viz_status_icon\": {\n    \"type\": \"icon_library.icon_library\",\n    \"dataSources\": { \"primary\": \"ds_health\" },\n    \"options\": {\n      \"backgroundColor\": \"transparent\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.iconName\": \"monitor_heart\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.showLabel\": \"yes\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.labelColor\": \"#CBD5E1\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.bgShape\": \"circle\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.bgColor\": \"#0F172A\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.bgPadding\": \"22\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.glow\": \"yes\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.glowSize\": \"14\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.colorGlow\": \"yes\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdLow\": \"70\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdHigh\": \"95\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdDirection\": \"high_good\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdIconLow\": \"error\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdIconMid\": \"warning\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdIconHigh\": \"check_circle\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdGlowScaleLow\": \"2\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdGlowScaleHigh\": \"0.6\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdPulse\": \"critical\",\n      \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdPulseSpeed\": \"1.2\",\n      \"drilldown\": \"all\"\n    },\n    \"eventHandlers\": [{\n      \"type\": \"drilldown.setToken\",\n      \"options\": {\n        \"tokens\": [\n          { \"token\": \"selected_service\", \"key\": \"label\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n> **Reminder:** `\"backgroundColor\": \"transparent\"` and `\"drilldown\": \"all\"` are **panel-level** Studio options (no `icon_library.icon_library.` prefix). All other options use the prefix.",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },

    "viz_sec9": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 9. Tips & See Also\n\n### Tips\n\n- **Auto-scaling:** Set `iconSize` and `labelSize` to `0` — the icon scales to fill the panel.\n- **No search required:** The icon renders from config alone; attach a search only for data-driven overrides or threshold-driven coloring.\n- **Background shapes** automatically encompass the icon and label together.\n- **Glow + Shadow** can be combined for depth effects.\n- **Rotation** applies to the icon (and background if present).\n- **Threshold colors + effects** can drive multiple elements at once — try `colorIcon=yes, colorGlow=yes` with `thresholdGlowScaleLow=2` for an emphatic critical-status tile.\n- **DOS expressions** on `iconColor` / `labelColor` / `glowColor` / `bgColor` flow through unchanged when the matching `colorIcon` / etc. toggle is set to `no` — use DOS for 5+ color bands.\n- **For drilldown to fire `setToken`**, the panel must use `ds.search` (not `ds.test`) and declare `\"drilldown\": \"all\"`.\n- **Custom icons:** Any name from [fonts.google.com/icons](https://fonts.google.com/icons) works — use `lowercase_with_underscores`.\n\n### See Also (bundled dashboards in this app)\n\n- **Service Health (Use Case)** — A realistic 6-tile service-status dashboard demonstrating threshold colors, threshold effects, and drilldown setToken in a production-style scenario. Look for it in the left-side nav.\n- **Icon Showcase** — All 256 popular icons across 17 themed sections, plus live demos of threshold colors, threshold effects, and drilldown. Useful as a visual catalog when picking an icon.\n\n---\n\n*Version 1.5.6 — Icon Library for Splunk Dashboard Studio*",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    }
  },

